    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Dorsally flattened mollusk with eight shell plates articulating dorsally, surrounded by a soft fleshy girdle. Girdle wide with spicules rising from chitinous cusps, corneous hairs scattered in bunches, some bearing a terminal spicule. Also with rectangular scales that have a concave base and rounded top. Articulamentum thick and whitish pink with subrectangular anterior extensions. Shell plates near rectangular but with round sides. Shell sculpture coarse with longitudinal riblets and pits on central area of middle plates and front of tail plate;&nbsp;radially arranged pustules on most areas. Brown or reddish pink.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_6115",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Small to medium, typically around 10-20 mm total body length.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_6116",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Namibia, South Africa, Mozambique, as well as Gough Island.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Namibia to Mozambique.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_6117",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Under rocks in the low-tidal and subtidal zone.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_6118",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Herbivorous - rasps algae off the rocks using its radula.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_6119",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>External fertilization, pelagic trochophore larvae metamorphizes and settles as juvenile chiton.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_6120",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>The radial numerous fine riblets on the side areas of the middle plate and the longitudinal fine riblets on the central and front tail plate areas separate <i>C. pertusa </i>from <i>C. pustulata </i>(KwaZulu-Natal). The granule sizes are small and prominent, while bigger in <i>C</i>. <i>pustulata </i>and less prominent <i>in C. papilio </i>(same region, but with very thick, dark spines covering the whole girdle)<i>.&nbsp;</i></p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_6121",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
